From: ArchSim project (S-06 U-ALS, v0.5.0 release)
Subject: [PATCH] Guard null AnimationInstance in AAlsCharacter::RefreshMeshProperties L400

Root cause [INFERRED from code pattern, evidence:
  Saved/Logs/ArchSim-backup-2026.06.28-03.37.00.log:L916-929]:
When AArchSimCharacter is spawned directly (no Blueprint child class wiring an
AnimBlueprint), GetMesh()->GetAnimInstance() returns null in
PostInitializeComponents(), leaving AnimationInstance unset (TWeakObjectPtr
not bound). All other AnimationInstance usage sites in this file already
guard with .IsValid() (lines 141, 156, 215, 260, 271, 1512) — this line was
the sole missing guard, causing EXCEPTION_ACCESS_VIOLATION on PIE start under
AArchSimGameMode.

AArchSimCharacter iter 2 (Source/ArchSim/Private/Characters/ArchSimCharacter.cpp)
uses LoadObject<> at PostInitProperties / BeginPlay timing to wire Settings,
MovementSettings, SkeletalMesh, AnimBlueprint. This guard is a defensive
second line of safety for headless / fixture builds where plugin content may
not be loaded.

Upstream issue: none filed yet (consider filing against ALS-Refactored v4.17+).
Tracked by Plugins/ALS/ untracked-third-party convention (see Tools/patches/README.md).

Apply with:
  cd <ArchSim repo root>
  git apply Tools/patches/als_l400_animinstance_guard.patch
OR (POSIX patch):
  patch -p1 < Tools/patches/als_l400_animinstance_guard.patch

---
 Plugins/ALS/Source/ALS/Private/AlsCharacter.cpp | 14 +++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/Plugins/ALS/Source/ALS/Private/AlsCharacter.cpp b/Plugins/ALS/Source/ALS/Private/AlsCharacter.cpp
index 0000000..0000001 100644
--- a/Plugins/ALS/Source/ALS/Private/AlsCharacter.cpp
+++ b/Plugins/ALS/Source/ALS/Private/AlsCharacter.cpp
@@ -397,6 +397,18 @@ void AAlsCharacter::RefreshMeshProperties() const

 	if (!bMeshIsTicking)
 	{
-		AnimationInstance->MarkPendingUpdate();
+		// FIX(v0.5.0 U-ALS, ArchSim project): guard against null AnimationInstance.
+		// Root cause [INFERRED from code pattern, evidence: ArchSim-backup-2026.06.28-03.37.00.log:L916-929]:
+		// when AArchSimCharacter is spawned directly (no BP child class wiring an
+		// AnimBlueprint), GetMesh()->GetAnimInstance() returns null in
+		// PostInitializeComponents(), leaving AnimationInstance unset. All other
+		// AnimationInstance uses in this file already guard with .IsValid()
+		// (lines 141, 156, 215, 260, 271, 409) — this line was the sole missing guard.
+		// AArchSimCharacter iter 2 uses LoadObject<> at PostInitProperties/BeginPlay
+		// timing to wire the AnimBP. This guard is a defensive second line of safety
+		// for headless / fixture builds where plugin content may not be loaded.
+		// Upstream issue: none filed yet.
+		if (AnimationInstance.IsValid())
+		{
+			AnimationInstance->MarkPendingUpdate();
+		}
 	}
 }
